		<div class="title">Re: Replacement Refs</div>
	
	<div class="content">
		<blockquote class="restore">From what I understand, the sticking point right now is the pension. They are part time employees and make from $3000 to $3500 per game. The refs want a pension plan and the owners don't want to pay it. Their stance is that they have many other part time and even full time employees that don't have a pension plan. <br />
<br />
So minimum, refs currently make $48k per season and that is for 16 regular season games. Add playoff and preseason, they make quite a bit. I can see the owners side in this. It's still a bad situation all around. My feeling is the owners should contribute to a 401 k plan. Up to a 2% match, which I think would be reasonable offer for the refs. Both sides should just go to arbitration in my opinion.</blockquote>
	</div>
